properties.headline: FLOODING - SINGLETON New England Highway
properties.adviceB: Exercise caution; 	Never drive through floodwater
properties.otherAdvice:
Northbound heavy vehicles are being stopped at the Golden Hwy at Whittingham.
Southbound heavy vehicles are being diverted in to Thomas Mitchell Dr at Muswellbrook.

There is currently no suitable diversion for heavy vehicles; operators of these vehicles should avoid the area or delay their journey.
properties.diversions:
Southbound light vehicles are being diverted at White Ave and can use Blaxland Ave and Bridgeman Rd to Obanvale. From there, use Retreat Rd, Dyrring Rd and Gresford Rd to join Queen St at Singleton. From Singleton, use local roads to rejoin the highway to continue travelling south.

Northbound light vehicles are being diverted at Pitt St and can use John St to travel to Queen St and Gresford Rd. From there, use Dyrring Rd and Retreat Rd to join Bridgman Rd at Obanvale. Travel south to Blaxland Ave then to White Ave to rejoin the New England Hwy.
